WorkItem.Description:
The callable vs. simple functions syntax is inconsistent

```
// Working
var x1 : (s: string)=>string; 
var x2 : { (s: string): string; }
interface x3{
	(s:string):string;
}

// Errors:
var y1 : (s: string):string;
var y2: { (s: string)=> string; }
interface y3{
	(s:string)=>string;
}
```

Some places ```:``` is appropriate, others ```=>``` is appropriate
